               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18420613-name-114" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18420613-name-114" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420613-name-114" type="surname" value="MALEY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420613-name-114" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS MALEY</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a police-constable, <hi rend="italic">H</hi> 74, but am suspended, in consequence of a robbery which took place on my beat, and about which I am now making inquiries; that is the reason of my being in plain clothes; I am not discharged. On the morning of the 2nd of June I was in St. Paul's Churchyard, and saw the prisoner draw a handkerchief from the prosecutor's left pocket with his left hand—I seized him—he directly put the handkerchief between his legs, and a companion that was with him took it from between his legs behind, and carried it off—it was a brownish coloured handkerchief, with spots on it.</p>
               <p>
